originalSql:
SELECT 
    a.name AS actor_name, 
    t.title AS movie_title, 
    t.production_year, 
    STRING_AGG(DISTINCT k.keyword, ', ') AS keywords, 
    c.kind AS company_type 
FROM 
    aka_name a 
JOIN 
    cast_info ci ON a.person_id = ci.person_id 
JOIN 
    aka_title t ON ci.movie_id = t.movie_id 
JOIN 
    movie_companies mc ON t.id = mc.movie_id 
JOIN 
    company_type c ON mc.company_type_id = c.id 
LEFT JOIN 
    movie_keyword mk ON t.id = mk.movie_id 
LEFT JOIN 
    keyword k ON mk.keyword_id = k.id 
WHERE 
    t.production_year >= 2000 
GROUP BY 
    a.name, t.title, t.production_year, c.kind 
ORDER BY 
    t.production_year DESC, a.name

INNER JOIN "aka_title" ON "cast_info"."movie_id" = "aka_title"."movie_id"
INNER JOIN "movie_companies" ON "aka_title"."id" = "movie_companies"."movie_id"
INNER JOIN "company_type" ON "movie_companies"."company_type_id" = "company_type"."id"
LEFT JOIN "movie_keyword" ON "aka_title"."id" = "movie_keyword"."movie_id"
LEFT JOIN "s1" ON "movie_keyword"."keyword_id" = "s1"."id"
WHERE "aka_title"."production_year" >= 2000
GROUP BY "aka_name"."name", "aka_title"."title", "aka_title"."production_year", "company_type"."kind"
ORDER BY "aka_title"."production_year" DESC NULLS FIRST, "aka_name"."name"
